# LittleJohn project infra secrets — COPY to `.env` (same dir) and fill in.
# `.env` is local-only, never committed, never pasted into chat.
# Every account below is SEPARATE from your personal stuff, created with the
# project email, hardware-key 2FA. Tokens are SCOPED (not global keys) so a leak
# has a small blast radius and can be rotated.

# --- Cloudflare (hosting + DNS + backend for littlejo.hn) ---
# dash.cloudflare.com → My Profile → API Tokens → Create Custom Token.
# Scope this ONE token for what we'll build over the next months (not "everything
# forever"). Include:
#   Account · Cloudflare Pages · Edit        (frontend hosting)
#   Account · Workers Scripts · Edit         (serverless API endpoints)
#   Account · Workers KV Storage · Edit      (leaderboard cache, config, proofs)
#   Account · Workers R2 Storage · Edit      (allocations.json, assets)
#   Account · D1 · Edit                      (SQL DB — points/leaderboard)
#   Account · Turnstile · Edit               (captcha / anti-sybil)
#   Zone · DNS · Edit                        (records for littlejo.hn)
#   Zone · Zone · Read
#   Zone · Cache Purge · Purge               (bust cache on deploy)
# Account Resources: this account. Zone Resources: littlejo.hn (+ .trading/.xyz).
# DO NOT add to this token (keep manual, behind hardware-2FA — a plaintext-.env token
# must not be able to escalate): API Tokens, Account Membership/Settings, Billing,
# Zero Trust/Access, SSL/Certificates, WAF/Firewall.
CLOUDFLARE_API_TOKEN=
CLOUDFLARE_ACCOUNT_ID=

# --- Supabase (OPTIONAL — only if we prefer Postgres over Cloudflare D1) ---
# With the Workers/D1/KV/R2 scope above, the whole points backend can run on
# Cloudflare and skip Supabase entirely. Fill these only if we choose Postgres.
# supabase.com → Account → Access Tokens, or use the Supabase MCP OAuth flow.
SUPABASE_ACCESS_TOKEN=
SUPABASE_PROJECT_REF=

# --- Deployer key (testnet) — lives in contracts/.env, NOT here ---
